## Description
The&nbsp;**Compress Files**&nbsp;task allows to&nbsp;compress the content to be included in the HTTP response of an on-demand application.

> Note

This task can be added before a final delivery task (such as the&nbsp;[Respond Content (HTTP)](/doxee-platform/docs/respond-content-http-on-demand-workflow-task-reference)&nbsp;task) in an on-demand workflow.

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the&nbsp;**Alias**&nbsp;field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the&nbsp;**Output** section, define a static or dynamic filename:

Enable the&nbsp;**Dynamic filename** option to&nbsp;copy the archive name from the output of the previous task, based on the configured parameters:![](data:image/png;base64,)

In the**&nbsp;Pattern** field, enter&nbsp;the filename pattern to use to identify the archive.

- In the&nbsp;**Filename**&nbsp;field,&nbsp;select the preferred option to inherit the archive name:

**Full name**: Full name, including base name and file extension

- **Base name**: Only the base name, without extension

- In the&nbsp;**Filename** field, enter the name of the file**&nbsp;**to create.
